oai_dc:dc.dc:title: No Loose Parts Necropsy Procedure for the Feedyard
oai_dc:dc.dc:creator: Griffin, Dee
oai_dc:dc.dc:subject: necropsy technique
body system
lymph node pathology
oai_dc:dc.dc:description: The necropsy technique outlined accomplishes three important objectives: 1) examination of all body systems, including the CNS, with the speed required to complete the procedure in less than 30 minutes; 2) targets identification of infectious disease in body systems through lymph node pathology; and 3) minimizes hide damage and detached body parts, both of which create serious problems for rendering companies.
oai_dc:dc.dc:source: American Association of Bovine Practitioners Conference Proceedings; 2003; 143-146
